<MELItem itemNbr="32-71-01" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.MEL.2-32-71-01.1.2-32-71-01">
<Title>Tail Strike Detector Channels</Title>
<MELSubItem itemNbr="32-71-01-01">
<Title>One Inoperative (*)</Title>
<DispatchCondition repairInterval="C" nbrInstalled="2" nbrRequired="1">
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>One may be inoperative.</Para>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
</DispatchCondition>
</MELSubItem>
<MELSubItem itemNbr="32-71-01-02">
<Title>Both Inoperative</Title>
<DispatchCondition repairInterval="C" nbrInstalled="2" nbrRequired="0" maintIndicator="(M)" opsIndicator="(O)">
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>May be inoperative provided:</Para>
<List listType="a.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Tail section is visually inspected for damage before each departure.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Alternate tail strike detection procedures are established and used.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>TAIL STRIKE caution message is disabled.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<DispatchProcedure>
<MaintenanceProcedure>
<Para>Before each departure, visually inspect the tail section of the aircraft for damage from a tail strike.</Para>
<Para>Disable the TAIL STRIKE caution message (AMM DDG 32-71-01).</Para>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Remove the Tail Strike Sensor (TSS).</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Fabricate a 4-6 inch long jumper using 22 gauge wire.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Effectivities>
<Effectivity>For 787-9 (VN-A861, VN-A862, VN-A863, VN-A864, VN-A865, VN-A866, VN-A867, VN-A868,
VN-A869, VN-A870, VN-A871)</Effectivity>
</Effectivities>
<Para>Install the jumper wire between the ship side pins A and B.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Effectivities>
<Effectivity>For 787-10 (VN-A872, VN-A873, VN-A874, VN-A877, VN-A878, VN-A879)</Effectivity>
</Effectivities>
<Para>Install the jumper wire between the ship side pins C and D.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Verify the following EICAS messages:</Para>
<List listType="A.">
<ListItem>
<Para>TAIL STRIKE caution is not displayed.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>TAIL STRIKE CHANNEL 1 status is not displayed.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>TAIL STRIKE CHANNEL 2 status is displayed.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Bag and stow the TSS connector. Cap the TSS receptacle.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Install the Tail Strike Sensor (TSS).</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</MaintenanceProcedure>
<OperationProcedure>
<Note>
<Para>The TAIL STRIKE caution message is not available.</Para>
</Note>
<Para>During takeoff and flare, flight crew and cabin crew should be alert for a potential tail strike. If a tail strike is perceived by the flight crew or reported from the cabin during takeoff, do the TAIL STRIKE Non-Normal Checklist.</Para>
</OperationProcedure>
</DispatchProcedure>
</DispatchCondition>
</MELSubItem>
</MELItem>
